algorithm: The new algorithm calculates the score for each bin by subtracting the square root of the maximum capacity minus the remaining capacity from the logarithm of the maximum capacity divided by the remaining capacity, and finally sorts the scores in descending order.
code:
import numpy as np

def score(item, bins):
    remaining_capacity = bins - item
    max_capacity = np.max(bins)
    scores = np.log(max_capacity / remaining_capacity) - np.sqrt(max_capacity - remaining_capacity)
    sorted_indices = np.argsort(scores)[::-1]
    scores = scores[sorted_indices]

    return scores
